name: Central Hobart Historic Cottage
description:
This renovated 1885 house has fantastic views & is an easy walk to city centre, or a stroll to the North Hobart cafe/restaurant strip.

It is a vegetarian household, so if you're a carnivore you'll need to engage your inner vego while at home :-)
neighborhood_overview: This part of West Hobart is heritage listed and one of the oldest parts of Hobart. It is very central, being on the edge of the CBD. There are many cafes, bars and restaurants nearby, with the cafe/restaurant strip in Elizabeth Street North Hobart a short walk away, and Salamanca a 20 minute walk. The renowned Hill Street Grocer is a 5 minute walk away if you want to stock up on quality food stuffs (they also sell prepared heat-and-eat meals), and Smolt Kitchen, Pigeon Whole Bakery Cafe & Room for a Pony are all great breakfast places and just a short stroll away.
host_about:
I am an adjunct Senior Lecturer at the School of Creative Arts & Media, University of Tasmania (and is fully vaccinated!)

Having felt like I was running an informal B&B for many years for friends and family, I  decided she may as well offer her home and hospitality to other travelers. I've been an AirBnB host for 12 years, and it has been a wonderful experience!

I am an artist, and animal advocate, and I love vegan cooking!

name: Kentisbury Country House Cradle Coast Tasmania
description: Kentisbury Country House is a gorgeous, self catering rural retreat, ideal for romantic couples, families and groups of up to nine friends. A perfect base for exploring Cradle Mountain National Park and the North Coast of Tasmania. The house is entirely yours to enjoy
neighborhood_overview: The European style house is situated on an acreage in the beautiful Kentish area with glorious views across rolling green fields towards Lake Barrington. Our guests enjoy hiking at Cradle Mountain, visiting the local vineyards, Anvers Chocolate Factory, Tasmazia, Ashgrove Cheese Factory, markets, galleries and the Outdoor Art Gallery town of Sheffield, famous for the murals. The coast is a half hour drive away and Mole Creek caves about the same distance.
host_about:
Life revolves around family, food and operating our accommodation business. Favourite holiday destinations, apart from our beautiful piece of the world, are Northern Italy, South West of France and Norway. We love to stay in self contained cottages, preferably with some history attached.
Five things we can't live without- Our children and grandchildren, good fresh organic food, long walks, chocolate and our Silkie chickens!

description:
A two storey 1880 terrace house.
Located in Hobart's CBD just mere minutes walking distance from the city's major cultural and gastronomic attractions including the historic precincts of Salamanca + Battery Point.

name: Cosy Cabin @ Eagles Rise - Cradle Mountain 1 hour
description:
Welcome to Eagles Rise and the Cosy Cabin, with the comfiest bed on the North Central Coast I'm told! A new bed and mattress is awaiting your review!
The Cosy Cabin is a unit joined on to the main house but separated by a hall and two double doors giving complete privacy.
On the Eastern side is the cabin garden with a picnic table & bench seats and a cafe table & two chairs, as well as a Weber BBQ to use.
You are up in the peaceful rural hills of Gawler yet only 10 mins from town and the beach!
neighborhood_overview:
A beautiful rural pocket of hills and valleys, with fresh air and lots of greenery!
And yet only 10 minutes to the town and beach!

Leven Canyon
Leven River Cruises with lunch
Gunns Plain Caves
Wing Wildlife Park
Lilico Beach Conservation Area, you will see Penguins from September to March.
Cradle Mountain and Dove Lake (80 km)
Narawntapu National Park (60 km)
Local Beaches - loads of them and mostly free of people!
Walking and cycling tracks
Vineyards
Turners Beach Berry Patch
Anvers Chocolate Factory
Mount Gnomon Farm
Penguin and the Sunday markets
host_about:
From London originally, now living here in Tasmania.
Love animals, nature, art, music and reading philosophy.  Still working on my second book The CANdida CANcer CONnection. The title of my first book is 'The Irritable Brain Syndrome'.
Love breathing the beautiful fresh air here in Tasmania and listening the the many different birds that visit during the seasons of the year.  My favourites are the swallows that visit every year, building their nests, teaching their young to fly!  And the eagles that cruise around on the winds, high up in the sky. That's awesome to see :)
If you like wallabies, possums, echidnas and rabbits, there is plenty of them around dawn and dusk!  They seem to like my place and also the vegetation! I have to keep an eye on my vegetable patch :)
I am the proud owner and protector of an Irish Wolfhound puppy (who will be 8 years young at the end of June 2023) and I greatly enjoy sharing this time with this beautiful gentle giant! 
Tippi is her name :)
My motto?  'The only thing I know, is that all that I know, is only true in the moment that I know it'  kc  :)
Practice Truth, Compassion and Tolerance and this world will become a better place for yourself and all who meet you :)
And I look forward to meeting you! :)
Here's a few places to check out 'just around the corner'! :)
Leven Canyon
Gunns Plain Caves
Wing Wildlife Park
Lilico Beach Conservation Area, you will see Penguins from September to March.
Cradle Mountain and Dove Lake (80 km)
Narawntapu National Park (60 km)
Local Beaches - loads of them!
Walking and cycling tracks
Vineyards
Turners Beach Berry Patch
Anvers Chocolate Factory, and many more.
See you soon! :)
Kit Campbell

name: 1950s 2BR Bicheno Holiday Cottage
description: Our 2BR cottage is perfectly located in Bicheno - 10 mins walk to both family friendly and great surf beaches. Only a 35min drive to Freycinet National Park and Wineglass bay. Great for couples or families exploring the East Coast or simply chilling
neighborhood_overview:
Bicheno has one of the mildest climates in Tasmania and is perfectly located to explore the East Coast or simply relax and enjoy what the town has to offer.

It's about 2 hours drive from Launceston, 2.5 hours from Hobart and 35 minutes from Freycinet National Park, Coles Bay and the famous Wineglass Bay. It's only about 15mins from the Douglas Apsley National Park which features a perfect water hole for swimming on a hot day.

We are also only about 40 mins from St Helens and Bay of Fires - the drive both north and south of Bicheno is amongst the most scenic routes in Tasmania.

It's also great for food lovers with summer berries, fresh fish, oysters, crayfish, wine, and several nice places to eat out all within easy access.

Bicheno is a small town but with great facilities including, an excellent bakery, an amazing fresh fish shop that also does great F'nC's, nice cafes and restaurants, a golf course and a lawn bowls and petanque club.
host_about: Greetings! We get down to Bicheno a couple of times a year, but we really want others to come and enjoy it! Bicheno and surrounds  have alot to offer but you can also do nothing but read or watch or play when you stay at Moonya! It is toasty warm when the fire is on, so even in the cooler months relaxation is to be had. Come, Enjoy, Relax! Melissa

name: Hideaway@Acton - a rustic cabin hidden in the bush
description: Ready for a bush hideaway? Hideaway@Acton is a rustic wood cabin located at the rear of my 2.5 acre property in Acton Park.    A feature of the cabin is the 'window wall' giving you uninterrupted views of the bushland, eucalyptus trees and the bird and animal life ! The property features one bedroom with ensuite bathroom and an open plan living space incorporating a kitchenette, dining and lounge area with sofabed.   Open the sliding door to a deck, the perfect spot to take in your surroundings!
neighborhood_overview: Acton Park is a semi-rural residential area, with most homes on acreage making it very private and peaceful.  The nearest shops are 5 minutes away (by car) in Lauderdale where you will find a small supermarket, chemist, newsagent, bottle shop and tavern, takeaway and coffee shops a 5  in Lauderdale.  Seven Mile and Roches Beach are a 5 minute drive, perfect spots for a swim or a beach walk.   Acton Park is conveniently located, approximately 15- 20 minutes to the heart of Hobart by car and a 10-15 minute drive to the Airport.
host_about:
Greetings to you and thanks for taking the time to delve a little more into my listing and profile.  I am truly blessed to live in the bushland environment that I do, with my 3 children, two dogs, a cat and chooks and the abundant wildlife that I share the land with. 

I love getting outdoors, whether it's working at home, walking the dogs or going bushwalking in our beautiful national parks.  I enjoy a regular yoga practice and continue to put myself out of my comfort zone by training with a karate group, ....... who said "you can't teach an old dog new tricks" !!!!

Tasmania has so many "hidden gems" to discover and I hope to spend more time travelling locally in the next few years.  I'm Tasmanian-born but continue to be amazed by what I've not seen before then stumble across.    When the time is right I'd love to head overseas again,  for another European adventure or trek the Inca Trail to Machu Picchu.

Tread lightly and travel safe on your journey,

Melissa

name: Families Groups & Couples ~ Fresh Coastal Shack
description:
'Sisters Beach Stay' is situated across the road, just a stone's throw from beautiful Sisters Beach.

Our 2 story stay is a modern version of the coastal shack - part shack and part home away from home.
We are a no-top-sheet kind of getaway, so you won't find ironed covers here; we embrace quirky with crinkles and a clean, fresh feel with a relaxed fit.
neighborhood_overview:
The village of Sisters Beach is enveloped on all sides by the spectacular Rocky Cape National Park.
Residents and visitors come here to enjoy the relaxed peaceful lifestyle, the unspoiled beaches, clear unpolluted waters, stunning coastal scenery, and secluded bush land. Take some time to stroll this long stretch of unspoiled beach, and marvel in the moody rock formations, powdery white sand and dark copper coloured tea tree water of Sisters Creek that flows into the ocean near your Stay.

Bushwalking, trekking or tramping (depending on where you come from), is one of the best ways to experience the beauty of nature, first hand. Using Sisters Beach Stays as your home base, you can adventure far and wide in a day and still enjoy the cosiness of the wood heater followed by a hot shower and a warm bed to soothe your weary bones at the end of the day.

Road trip for the day or stay and explore our local region. We are more than happy to assist with recommendatio

name: The Lazy Prospector. Central Wilderness Stay for 2
description:
An ideal central base to explore Tasmania‚Äôs rugged west coast, and the perfect place for you and your special someone to relax after a day of hiking, biking or sightseeing.

Whether it‚Äôs the deep soak bath, lounging in front of the wood fire heater, or relaxing on the daybed while taking in the mountain views, special memories are made here.

The Lazy Prospector, featured in Broadsheet and Qantas Insider, welcomes guests of all communities and backgrounds.
neighborhood_overview:
The West Coast is as rugged, magnificent, and photogenic as it is soothing to the soul.

Zeehan, where The Lazy Prospector is located, has a rich and colourful history. Once known as The Silver City, in the early 1900s, it was home to 10,000 people and a bustling mining community. At the time, it was the third largest town in Tasmania.

Today, the faded glamour of these heady days is captured by the hauntingly beautiful grand buildings lining the main street, while a grittiness, remnant of its mining days, is evident throughout. The hauntingly beautiful Main Street can, at times, feel like a modern day ghost town.

Zeehan is central to all the west coast towns:

- Queenstown (30 mins drive) home to the Westcoast Wilderness Railway, Empire Hotel and the contemporary Q Bank Gallery;

- Rosebery (20 mins drive) a working mining town where you‚Äôll discover Montezuma Falls;

name: Binalong Bay Beach House
description: Set in beautiful Binalong Bay, this modern 4-bedroom house has views over the beach and up to Eddystone Point. It boasts a large open plan light-filled living area with a large kitchen that all the family can enjoy. A short stroll down the street you have the choice of swimming in secluded and sheltered Gulches or a little further to the world-renowned Binalong Bay Beach and Bay of Fires. Whilst you're in the area call into the Easy Tiger complex for a coffee or a cocktail in the beer garden.
neighborhood_overview: Binalong Bay is a very exclusive seaside village and is the gateway to the Bay of Fires.  The village has amazing gulches for swimming or exploring with lichen red rocks, a great protected boat ramp, and great beaches with the whitest sand and great surfing.    Binalong Bay has several coffee shops and a great restaurant and is only 10 minutes out of St Helens.
